11/04/2010
PRAGUE, Czech Republic -- Romanian President Traian Basescu announced on Thursday (April 8th) that his country will boost its contingent to Afghanistan from 1,073 to 1,800 troops by September. 
Basescu made the statement before leaving for Prague to attend a working dinner with US President Barack Obama along with other leaders from Central and Eastern Europe. 
The decision to send extra troops to Afghanistan was made in March. 
(Realitatea - 09/04/10; AP, Mediafax - 08/04/10)
